    "recap_headline": "TCU",
    "recap_text": "FORT WORTH\n\u2013 TCU dropped a 9-1 decision in the series finale against UCF on Sunday afternoon at Lupton Stadium.\nSawyer Strosnider\nhit his eighth home run of the season in the loss.\nThe Rundown\nEarly offense and a strong outing from its starter put UCF on the path to victory. The Knights took an early 3-0 lead in the first and never looked back. They added two in the third and one in the fourth to open up a 6-0 lead. The Knights tacked on its final three runs with two outs in the seventh.\nWhile the Horned Frogs struggled to find hits, they had base runners in seven of the nine innings.\nJack Bell\nregistered TCU's first hit of the afternoon, a double to lead off the sixth.\nSawyer Strosnider\nwon a 13-pitch at-bat with a solo home run with two outs in the eighth to account for TCU's lone run.\nTrever Baumler\ntook the loss after giving up five runs on six hits in two innings.\nNate Stern\ngave the Frogs 1 1/3 scoreless.\nNoah Franco\nmade his return to the mound in the ninth.\nTyler Phenow\ngot the only batter he faced to ground into a double play.\nStat of the Game:\n3 \u2013\nTCU had just three hits in the game, its second-lowest output of the season.\nNotes:\n\u2022 TCU homered in a game for the 16\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 TCU allowed a first inning run for ninth time this season.\n\u2022 TCU turned three double plays in the game.\n\u2022\nSawyer Strosnider\nhit his eighth home run of the season and the 19\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nColton Griffin\nhas reached safely in 14 straight games.\n\u2022\nLucas Franco\nhas reached safely in six straight games.\nNext Up:\nWith the loss, TCU falls to 13-10 on the season and 2-4 in Big 12 play.\u00a0TCU will hit the road for a midweek tilt at DBU Tuesday night. First pitch is set for 6:30 p.m. The game will be televised on ESPN+.",
